UID:68534-1792972800-1793231999@ontarionature.org
SUMMARY:OLTA's Annual Gathering
DESCRIPTION:It’s official – the 2026 Gathering will be October 26th – 28th!\nThis year’s Gathering will be held at Horseshoe Valley Resort in Barrie\, on the traditional territory of the Anishinaabe and Huron-Wendat peoples\, in the area of the Williams Treaties and Lake Simcoe Treaty 16. \nThe address is 1101 Horseshoe Valley Road West\, Barrie\, L4M 4Y8.   \nWe are in the early stages of planning and further information on the schedule\, sessions\, registration\, and more will follow in the coming months. \nFor now\, please mark the dates in your calendar as we’d love to see all of you there!  \nWe are looking for committee members to help with session development and coordination! Committee members would attend one or two meetings per month in the leadup to the Gathering\, as well as contact\, confirm\, and coordinate with speakers for the sessions they are coordinating. If you are interested in participating on the committee or have questions\, please reach out to Erinn at erinn.todd@olta.ca by March 27th.
URL:https://ontarionature.org/event/oltas-annual-gathering/
LOCATION:Horseshoe Valley Resort\, 1101 Horseshoe Valley Road West
CATEGORIES:Nature Network,Ontario Land Trust Alliance,Provincial Partners
ORGANIZER;CN="Ontario Land Trust Alliance":MAILTO:phyllis.lee@olta.ca
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR